# Validator:            https://github.com/citation-file-format/cff-converter-python

cff-version: 1.2.0

message: >-
  If you reference AAEP (the Agent Accessibility Event Protocol) in
  academic publications, industry reports, technical documentation,
  standards proposals, or related materials, please cite this
  repository using the metadata below.

title: "AAEP: Agent Accessibility Event Protocol"

abstract: >-
  AAEP (Agent Accessibility Event Protocol) is an open protocol that
  enables AI agents to communicate their lifecycle, state, tool
  invocations, and confirmation requests to assistive technology in a
  standardized, vendor-neutral, programming-language-neutral format.
  AAEP defines a wire format, a subscription handshake, a confirmation
  reply mechanism, and an extension model that together let any
  AAEP-compliant agent interoperate with any AAEP-compliant assistive
  technology, including screen readers, voice control, switch control,
  and assistive devices yet to be invented. The protocol is designed
  to coexist with the Model Context Protocol (MCP) and to be
  integrable into any agent framework (Microsoft Agent Framework,
  AutoGen, LangChain, Semantic Kernel, the Anthropic SDK, custom
  implementations) without requiring framework-specific libraries
  from the AAEP project itself.

